    subgraph U2["Unit 2: Period 2 - 1607 to 1754"]
        U2S1["England colonized America for economic opportunity, religious freedom, and rivalry with other nations"]
        U2S2["Jamestown (1607) was the first permanent English settlement in America"]
        U2S3["Joint-stock companies like the Virginia Company funded English colonization"]
        U2S4["Tobacco became Virginia's main cash crop and created a huge demand for labor"]
        U2S5["The headright system gave land to people who paid for workers to come to Virginia"]
        U2S6["The Chesapeake colonies gradually shifted from using indentured servants to enslaved Africans"]
        U2S7["The Separatist Pilgrims founded Plymouth Colony in 1620"]
        U2S8["The Puritans founded Massachusetts Bay Colony, aiming to build a 'city upon a hill'"]
        U2S9["Puritan religious beliefs heavily influenced how New England was governed and organized"]
        U2S10["The Mayflower Compact was an early example of colonists governing themselves"]
        U2S11["Town meetings were a form of direct democracy in New England"]
