        U2S13["Anne Hutchinson challenged Puritan authority in the Antinomian Controversy"]
        U2S14["The New England, Middle, and Southern colonies had major differences from each other"]
        U2S15["New England's economy was based on trade, fishing, shipbuilding, and small farms"]
        U2S16["The Middle Colonies were ethnically diverse, grew lots of grain, and had mixed economies"]
        U2S17["The Southern Colonies' economy was built on cash crops and plantation farming"]
        U2S18["William Penn founded Pennsylvania as a Quaker colony with religious tolerance"]
        U2S19["Plantation farming in the South created an ever-growing demand for labor"]
