        U2S36["The First Great Awakening was a religious revival that challenged established church authority"]
        U2S37["Jonathan Edwards and George Whitefield were key figures in the Great Awakening"]
        U2S38["The Great Awakening encouraged individual thinking and questioning traditional authority"]
        U2S39["Enlightenment ideas spread through an Atlantic intellectual community connecting America and Europe"]
        U2S40["Key Enlightenment ideas included natural rights, reason, and the social contract"]
        U2S41["Salutary neglect was Britain's practice of loosely enforcing colonial rules"]
        U2S42["Because Britain didn't enforce rules strictly, the colonies developed traditions of self-government"]
        U2S43["Colonial assemblies like the Virginia House of Burgesses were important self-governing institutions"]
